  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So-- but in all kinds of ways, you were made to feel separate and that you were not judged by the same standards.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Your marks tended to be lower.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You had to work twice as hard to even get the same marks, never mind better marks, and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--very very early.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the only way in which I could express this was by joining a Zionist organization, which I found out existed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was the Habonim.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was a member of the Habonim.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father was, was in favor, which was very, very generous of him because his own convictions were quite the other way.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was not a Zionist.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in, in Germany, as in other places, there were two large categories of Jews, one assimilated and one Zionist.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In Germany, the division was particularly strong, particularly direct, because the Jews were, by and large, the professional classes, the business classes, and they were pretty well off.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
